description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced and dynamic Occupational Therapist with developed skills and experience in treating complex service users with experience in stroke &amp; neurological care, who is passionate about therehabilitation of older people inthe community hospital setting?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Are you looking to develop skills in leadership and management, within a supportive environment allowing you to lead&amp; manage the Therapyteams to assess people in a timely way, whilstbeing focused on supporting rehabilitation through self-management, optimising of personal goals and independence?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a 1 year fixed term contract for a full time (37.5 hr)&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;lead therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. The successful candidate will join a committed multidisciplinary team working across two community hospital wards and be part of an exciting new therapy-led inpatient bedded unit, supportingeffective dischargethrough re-enabling care and therapy. They will also work in conjunction with the ward managers to manage the inpatient OT and Physio teams across site in implementing service development projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Valued&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As anOccupational TherapistdeliveringNHSservices with us you will receiveAfC 20/21 salary and terms and conditions,including an NHS pension.We’ll provide you with access to a committed Learning and Development team, and we work closely with Universities and Health Education England to further your potential and support your progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will become part of the Virgin Tribe. This grants you access to premier offers and discounts on Virgin Products such as holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll access our central online health and lifestyle platform covering healthy recipes, activity challenges, and support information around mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Proud&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have yourBSC degree in Occupational Therapy as well as having your HCPC registration.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an experiencedOccupational Therapistyou willdeliverindividualised and evidence based care to all patients, focusing on self-care and independence through rehabilitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within theMulti-disciplinaryteam, you willworkacross two community ward sites including the therapy focused beds at St Martins Hospital, as part of a 7 day service.You’ll care for patients and their families in the way thatyou believe is best, delivering our high service standards, sharing bestpractice, and actively improving the way we work to help us change things for the better. We feel passionate that everyone should feel valued when they come into contact with our organisation, whether that&#39;s you, someone we care for or the wider community we operate in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be based primarily inSt Martins &amp; Paulton Community Hospitals in Bath &amp; North East Somerset&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have built organisation-wide committees in many specialist fields. You’ll have the option to join your clinical specialism, networking with professionals from across the country. We get together regularly, auditing and sharing standard methodology for innovation and service re-design. You’ll be a part of the pool of subject matter experts bringing together clinical and operational leads. You will be a part of quality improvements, research and development activity. Here we recognise and celebrate clinical excellence and dedication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel the Difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’d like to discuss the role further, please contactLucy Comervia email:lucy.comer&lt;em&gt;@&lt;/em&gt;virgincare.co.ukor on the phone 07813 586 974&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Virgin Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to equal opportunities and welcome a broad diversity of talent to apply. We reserve the right to cease any advertising prior to the published closing date for a role that receives a high number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Disability Confident Committed company, we work in partnership with the Department of Work and Pensions (DWP) to provide facilities, work environment adjustments and technical solutions to make our business an inclusive place for all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Virgin Care Limited, its subsidiary companies and the Virgin Care LLPs are part of the Virgin Group and provide publicly funded health and social care services. If you would like to know a little more about how we use your information, please see our website’s privacy policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
